---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import SectionReveal from "./SectionReveal.tsx";
import headshot from "../assets/liam.jpeg";
---

<section id="about" class="py-20">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
    <SectionReveal client:visible>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-serif text-text-primary mb-8">About</h2>
      <div
        class="bg-surface-raised border border-border-subtle rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 hover:border-accent/30 transition-colors shadow-sm"
      >
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center sm:flex-row sm:items-start gap-6">
          <Image src={headshot} alt="Liam Sheehan" width={128} height={128} class="w-32 h-32 rounded-full object-cover border-2 border-accent shrink-0" />
          <div>
            <p class="text-text-primary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              I design and build interactive learning experiences that drive
              measurable outcomes. From branching scenarios in Articulate Storyline
              to custom web-based simulations, my work centers on scenario-based
              learning, meaningful feedback loops, and learner-centered evaluation.
              I combine instructional design expertise with hands-on development skills.
            </p>
            <p class="text-text-primary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              My background in game design shapes how I think about engagement,
              learner agency, and feedback loops. Every interaction should feel
              purposeful. An MS in Instructional Design grounds that instinct in
              evidence-based practice: clear learning objectives, authentic
              assessments, and iterative design informed by research.
            </p>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              I bring ideas to life as functional prototypes so stakeholders can
              experience the learning before it ships. My toolkit includes
              Articulate Storyline, Articulate Rise, React, TypeScript, Astro,
              and Twine, all applied in service of learning, rather than
              technology for its own sake.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </SectionReveal>
  </div>
</section>
